==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Partite
<hw>Par"tite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>partitus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>partire</ets> to part, divide, from
<ets>pars</ets>. See <er>Part</er>, and cf. <er>Party</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Divided nearly
to the base; <as>as, a <ex>partite</ex> leaf is a simple separated down
nearly to the base</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of parts; usually used in compounds
specifying the number of parts; <as>as, a tri<ex>partite</ex>
treaty</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Partition</ent>⟦br⟧
